izing photon rate of the\nquasar. If both the quasar position and its luminosity are known, the\nredshifted 21 cm data can set new constrains on quasar lifetimes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 2 Mar 2012 16:33:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 10 May 2012 08:34:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
